BARD HELP

Welcome to the Bard guild. Bards win through momentum, timing, morale,
misdirection, and the right instrument in the right moment. This help system is
meant to walk you from your first guild level into the deeper song system.

If you are new, read these in order:

  bardhelp start          Your first checklist as a Bard.
  bardhelp general        What Bards are good at and how they play.
  bardhelp songs          Performance, song forms, and hidden harmonies.
  bardhelp patterns       Reviewing harmonies and pivots you have learned.
  bardhelp instruments    Lutes, drums, flutes, harps, and other tools.
  bardhelp combat         How to use songs during fights.
  bardhelp support        How to help a party or a room.
  bardhelp archetypes     Guild level 10 specializations.
  bardhelp commands       Guild-level command list.

Useful daily commands:

  bscore                  Show Bard stats, instrument, archetype, Performance.
  bpatterns               Show hidden harmonies and pivots you have learned.
  bmon on                 Show Bard updates without typing bscore constantly.
  bcmds                   Show your Bard commands in a level-friendly format.
  fix lute                Restore your guild lute from anywhere.
  instrument              Show and select carried Bard instruments.
  help <command>          Show exact syntax for one command.

Other topics:

  bardhelp communication  Guild channels and Bard communication.
  bardhelp ranks          Old Bard rank lore and titles.
  bardhelp lute           Instrument and lute reference.

The short version: keep music moving, vary your song forms, watch Performance,
learn what your instrument changes, and at guild level 10 choose an archetype
that matches the way you want to perform.
